wiki_section_title: Classification -- Qualifying

wiki_section_text: 

intro: The 1950 Italian Grand Prix was a Formula One motor race held on 3 September 1950 at Autodromo Nazionale Monza. It was race 7 of 7 in the 1950 World Championship of Drivers. In this race, Nino Farina became the first World Drivers' Champion, and the only driver to win the title in his home country.
